MESSAGE: - clears throat -
Many, many moons ago, the first cats came into the world. They worked and lived together in harmony.
They were the Wind Tribe, lean, sturdy cats that lived in the forest.
They were lead by Wind Speaker, an old grey tabby, the first cat created by Silverpelt. She had seen the first rise of the sun, and had heard the first whisper of the world.
The forest was a bloody time back then, and even though they lived as one, they faced constant threats, and Wind Speaker could only do so much.
Wind Speaker knew that she wouldn't be here to guide her cats forever, but she didn't know who else would... or even who could
There were, however, three young cats who had noticed Wind Speaker's weakening age.
These cats were Running Water, Scorching Fire, and Rising Dawn, Wind Speaker's own daughter.
They all worried for their leader, Rising Dawn especially.
In secret, all of their tribemates wanted one of them to challenge Wind Speaker for the position of leader.
Then, on a starry night, Wind Speaker died.
It was chaotic, and many cats died. In the end, the remaining cats split into three groups to claim their own land.
Rising Dawn kept her group in the forest, where she had learned to hunt only by moonlight under the tree's canopy.
Running Water left to the island, where he had felt protected by its comforting waters.
And Scorching Fire went to the moor, where she could feel the wind in her fur, and see the stars of the night.
Split into groups, the cats were even more vulnerable... sickness was everywhere, and so were enemies.
When leaf-bare came, things only got worse.
No cat was ever full, and several starved.
One by one, the groups started to thin out, them as well as the rouges that had joined them.
On a dark night, Rising Dawn called for all three groups to gather at High Rocks.
A battle broke out, and many were wounded...
But then, out of the mist, Wind Speaker appeared.
She scolded the cats, for letting fear and hunger sharpen their claws.

She told the cats this,"If you agree to live in peace, I will come down from the stars and give you a place to live, prey to hunt, and the ability to live without fear of what is walking the forest alongside you.
The cats agreed, and Wind Speaker, true to her word, kept her promise.
She knocked down a tree to guard the hollow of where Rising Dawn, later Dawnstar, would make her camp.
She scooped out the dip where Scorching Fire would make her camp and earn the name Firestar.
And she parted the river to protect Running Water and her cats, who would learn to call her by the name of Wavestar
The cats too, have kept their word, but I sense change coming, a dark time...
- clears throat -
This is the story of how I lost my eyesight.
As you may know, my name as a rouge was Nettle, after the medicinal plant.
As a rouge, I lived with my sister Rose
Rose was a tortoiseshell.
Our den was an old badger set, where we knew no other animal would enter.
However one day, we scented something odd while returning home...
It was a fox, twice the size of us....
Rose and I fought the fox, slashing and biting, matching each other pawstep for pawstep.
Then, as I was about to leap onto its back, it turned on me
I tried to dodge out of the way, but it caught me first.
It slashed across my face, permanently damaging my eyesight.
Blindly, I ran as far away as I could...
Sadly, it killed Rose, I found out when I returned to the den the next sunrise.
- clears throat -
You might've noticed that one of our warriors, Stormtail, has a deep red collar.
In truth... Stormtail wasnt born in Dawnclan, they used to belong to a rouge group.
Stormtail joined Dawnclan after Fireclan's leader, Firestar, led a patrol to end them and the other rouges
Stormtail was challenged to enter the clan... against Dawnstar herself.
Little did anyone know... the only reason Stormtail, back then Storm, was alive...
... Was because they had been able to take the first life of Firestar, and fought their way out.
Dawnstar herself almost lost a life too. When going full out, Stormtail and Dawnstar fight on the same level.
Just remember this the next time you're training with them... You're training with one of the strongest warriors to have ever walked this forest
Maybe next time?
